Emir of Fika and Chairman Yobe State Council of Chiefs, Dr. Muhammad Ibn Abali Muhammad Idrissa, has warned the public against indiscriminate dumping of refuse and building on water ways across the state. The emir, who gave out the warning in a statement by his media aide, Alhaji Mohammed Abubakar, said the excessive rainfall being recorded recently is a clear warning for people to avoid the practice. “We must do our part as human beings, take advantage of the rainfall by fully embracing farming and pray for bumper harvest,” he advised. The monarch also called on his subject to monitor the behavior of their children and live peacefully with each other irrespective of religious or cultural differences. “I wish to appeal to you to live in harmony with one another, live peacefully, report any suspicious movements to the security agencies, watch the behavior of your wards and pray for bumper harvest this rainy season”, he added. The emir also called on the people to support government policies and programs to enable them benefited more from the dividend of democracy.  2019: Emir of Fika cautions against violence 2019 polls: Emir of Fika urges candidates to eschew violence Zazzau Emir laments frequent cases of rape of minors Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin